===message:You make a good point regarding the “romantic idea” of WW1 Wendy. World War One was fought by young men who believed in a just cause, yet who were naïve in their view of life. They went to war thinking they would fight a romantic war, only to find themselves in mud and death which they could not stop, in a war controlled by senior officers brought up on unrealistic tactical methods and with no realistic alternatives. In the end the politics of this war were insignificant compared to the feelings, fear, and experience of the individual men and what they thought of this appalling, pointless, and inhuman tragedy.



=========yorg=========
