===message:I think the fact that people were so proud to be a citizen of whichever country that they came from and the strong sense of duty to ones country was the reason that parents were proud of their sons who served in the war. The parents probably did know the risks that their child would be taking but there was really no way to prevent the government from calling on their young men to serve their country. 
